WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.480
So today my topic is Epcoid Tumor Plus GDB for Relapsed Refractory Diffused Large B-Cell Lymphoma.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:07.700
These are my financial disclosures.

00:00:08.540 --> 00:00:14.060
So patients who have relapsed or primary refractory disease, particularly large B-cell lymphoma,

00:00:14.360 --> 00:00:19.220
they receive CAR-T-cell therapy or autologous stem cell transplantation as a curative modality,

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:21.460
depending on the timing of the relapse.

00:00:21.940 --> 00:00:26.660
However, patients who have large cell lymphoma, and particularly those with rapidly progressing

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:31.680
and symptomatic disease, often require bridging treatment while awaiting CAR-T-cell therapy.

00:00:32.140 --> 00:00:36.760
In general, the median time from vein to vein timing is approximately 8 to 10 weeks.

00:00:36.860 --> 00:00:39.320
So those are the patients in need of further treatment.

00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:44.400
So the effective salvage or bridging chemotherapy, which offers high response rates, controls

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:48.580
the disease, is highly is warranted to improve outcomes of these patients.

00:00:49.420 --> 00:00:55.320
So Epcoid Tumor, as the audience is very well aware, is a CD3, CD20 targeting bispecific

00:00:55.320 --> 00:00:55.800
antibody.

00:00:56.400 --> 00:01:00.720
And it is approved for relapsed large B-cell lymphoma after two prior lines of therapies.

00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:05.860
There are emerging data showing high level of synergy between Bispecific and

00:01:05.860 --> 00:01:06.260
chemotherapy.

00:01:07.020 --> 00:01:13.600
So we propose the Phase II IIT, evaluating safety and efficacy of Epcoid Tumor and GDP,

00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:19.360
which is gemcitabine, dexamethasone, and cisplatinum among relapsed refractory large B-cell lymphoma

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.340
eligible for CAR-T-cell therapy or stem cell transplant.

00:01:23.220 --> 00:01:26.380
These are the key eligibility criteria patients have to have.

00:01:26.380 --> 00:01:30.620
If they have relapsed CD20-positive large B-cell lymphoma, they should have received

00:01:30.620 --> 00:01:35.400
at least one prior line of systemic therapy for large B-cell lymphoma, and they should

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:39.760
be eligible for stem cell transplant or CAR-T-cell therapy per physician discretion.

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:48.200
Key exclusion criterias were receipt of any CD3, CD20 Bispecific or any of the

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:50.420
component of GDP chemotherapy.

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:52.940
So this is a study chemo.

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:55.940
This was a finite duration, three cycles of treatment.

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:58.140
Each cycle consists of three weeks.

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:06.080
Epcoid Tumor was given in the standard step-up doses, 0.16 during week 1, 0.8 week 2, and

00:02:06.080 --> 00:02:10.500
48 milligrams week 3 onwards, and each cycle consisted of three weeks.

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:14.500
GDP was also given in the standard fashion, two weeks on, one week off.

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:17.060
This was strictly an outpatient regimen.

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:22.460
No inpatient hospitalization following first full dose of Epcoid Tumor for CRS monitoring

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:23.120
was mandatory.

00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:26.100
The key objectives were.

00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:30.880
Complete response rates per Lugano classifications, and there were other secondary objectives

00:02:30.880 --> 00:02:35.180
including overall response rate, duration of response, progression-free and overall

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:40.980
survival, safety and tolerability, and most importantly, feasibility of stem cell mobilization

00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:43.860
or CAR-T-cell therapy.

00:02:43.860 --> 00:02:50.020
This trial was designed for Simon-Tustin design, and this data reflects the first stage of

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:54.160
preliminary efficacy, and most importantly, the decision to move forward to Simon's

00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:55.540
second stage of the study.

00:02:55.540 --> 00:02:59.980
Total 14 patients were enrolled during Simon's first stage design.

00:03:00.420 --> 00:03:03.520
Majority of the patients had advanced large B-cell lymphoma.

00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:08.440
Double and triple-A lymphoma, double-X-presso lymphoma represented approximately one-third

00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:09.580
of the entire population.

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:18.320
40% of patients had primary refractory disease, and close to 55-57% of patients had germinal

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:25.520
center as a cell of oresine, and prior lines of therapies were won, and, sorry, medium-prior

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:30.200
lines of prior therapies were two in the majority of the patients.

00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:34.760
So, as you can see, the primary objectives were complete response rates, and they were

00:03:34.760 --> 00:03:41.080
64%, and the study met the primary endpoint.

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:45.780
All patients received protocol-defined three cycles of efcoetamab and GDP.

00:03:45.780 --> 00:03:50.500
All patients underwent successful stem cell mobilization or peripheral blood T-lymphocyte

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:51.500
collections.

00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:52.300
Out of 14 patients when the data were analyzed, seven patients already received stem cell mobilization.

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:53.300
Out of 14 patients when the data were analyzed, seven patients already received stem cell mobilization.

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:54.300
Out of 14 patients when the data were analyzed, seven patients already received stem cell mobilization.

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:55.300
Out of 14 patients when the data were analyzed, seven patients already received stem cell mobilization.

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:59.700
stem cell transplant, and three patients received CD19-directed CAR-T cell therapy.

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:06.560
The follow-up is extremely short at six months, but at median duration of response was not reached.

00:04:07.020 --> 00:04:14.640
Median PFS was not reached, but at six-month PFS was 74%. The safety profile was most important

00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:19.820
to us. I just wanted to make sure that the addition of APCO to GDP does not increase the

00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:24.480
safety profile, and safety profile was highly consistent with what we observed with the salvage

00:04:24.480 --> 00:04:30.800
chemotherapy, including cytopenias and fatigue and increased risk of infection. The CRS summary

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:38.940
was quite favorable. Incidence of CRS was 50%. The time of onset of CRS from cycle one day one

00:04:38.940 --> 00:04:44.600
was 16 days, which is just roughly a day after the first full dose. Time to resolution of CRS

00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:49.780
was within a day. Number of patients who require hospitalization for CRS were just one patient,

00:04:49.780 --> 00:04:53.660
so it shows us that this is an outpatient-based regimen and

00:04:53.660 --> 00:04:59.860
can safely be delivered, and majority of the patients had milder CRS and two patients required

00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:07.100
tocilizumab for CRS management. So, in conclusion, APCO retumab and GDP regimen demonstrated early

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:13.420
signal of efficacy in relapsed refractory large B-cell lymphoma. This regimen is feasible to

00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:20.320
administer in the outpatient setting as a bridge or salvage regimen prior to CAR-T cell therapy or

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:22.980
stem cell transplant without adversely impacting stem cell transplant. So, this is an outpatient-based

00:05:22.980 --> 00:05:31.860
regimen. The study matches its primary endpoint and continues to enroll with the final accrual of 32

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:38.100
patients. As of a month ago, the study has enrolled 28 patients, so we are a little less than four

00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:42.660
patients or so to finish this trial. With that, I would like to conclude. Thank you so much.
